cs.CY, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses a scheme to discourage ghost authorships and increase credit to a paper when co-authorships increase. While the paper does not focus on a specific area of computer science, it is relevant to several sub-categories such as cyberspace security (cs.CR), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and possibly computational complexity (cs.CY) as well. Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
